r of Rhode Island]]: [[J. Joseph Garrahy]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of South Carolina]]: [[Richard Riley]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of South Dakota]]: [[William J. Janklow]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Tennessee]]: [[Lamar Alexander]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Texas]]: [[Bill Clements]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Utah]]: [[Scott M. Matheson]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Vermont]]: [[Richard A. Snelling]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Virginia]]: [[John N. Dalton]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Washington]]: [[Dixy Lee Ray]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (until January 14), [[John Spellman]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) (starting January 14)\n* [[Governor of West Virginia]]: [[Jay Rockefeller]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Governor of Wisconsin]]: [[Lee S. Dreyfus]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Governor of Wyoming]]: [[Edgar J. Herschler]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]])\n}}\n\n=== Lieutenant governors ===\n{{columns-list|colwidth=30em|\n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Alabama]]: [[George McMillan (politician)|George McMillan]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Alaska]]: [[Terry Miller (politician)|Terry Miller]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governor of Arkansas]]: [[Joe Purcell]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (until January 19), [[Winston Bryant]] ([[Democratic Party (United States)|Democratic]]) (starting January 19)\n* [[Lieutenant Governor of California]]: [[Mike Curb]] ([[Republican Party (United States)|Republican]]) \n* [[Lieutenant Governo